 By Dirisu Yakubu, Abuja Nigeria’s representative at the International Civil Aviation Organization, ICAO, Council, Captain Musa Nuhu has been elected chairman by the Comprehensive Regional Implementation Plan for Aviation Safety in Africa and the Indian Ocean, AFI, Plan Steering Committee in Montreal Canada. The election took place on Thursday during the AFI Plan Steering Committee meeting at the ongoing 40th Session of ICAO General Assembly, where Capt. Nuhu succeeded Mr. Halidou Moussa, who has been heading the group since 2013. Continue reading NIGERIA’s ICAO representative elected chairman, AFI committee at Vanguard Nigeria. Source: Vanguard